@PommeVerte ,

The line of CSS you mention is in there, however, if you wrap your input in form tags, and have styling like `form input {display:block}` that should take precedence.

There is another problem putting form fields in using `html: true`, because everything in `text` gets wrapped in `<p>...</p>`, and it is invalid to have form elements inside `p` tags. I fixed this locally by switching the `p` tags for divs. I will fork and submit a pull request; you are welcome to checkout my fork.

